		<body>
			<div type="original">
				<p>
					<lb facs="#zone_tvt_kky_r2b"/> 渋谷新平二入道
					<lb facs="#zone_qb2_lky_r2b"/>
					<persName corresp="#入来院重基">定円</persName>
					<name corresp="https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q11487841" type="keyword"
						>当知行</name>地、不可
					<lb facs="#zone_mkn_lky_r2b"/>有相違者、
					<lb facs="#zone_hnw_lky_r2b"/> 天気如此、悉之以状、
					<lb/> 　　　<seg facs="#zone_rwf_mky_r2b"><date when="1333-12-16"
						>元弘三年十一月九日</date></seg>　　　　　　　　　<seg facs="#zone_hmw_mky_r2b"><name
							corresp="#式部大丞" type="keyword" ref="http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q3727885">式部大丞</name></seg><seg
						facs="#zone_nst_nky_r2b">（花押）</seg>
					<lb/>
				</p>
			</div>
			<div type="english">

				<p>
					<lb/><seg xml:id="noteEn1-1-1">THE land in actual holding</seg> of Shibuya
					Shin-hei-zhi <emph rend="italic">nyu-do</emph>
					<persName corresp="#入来院重基"><seg xml:id="noteEn1-1-2">Jo-Yen</seg></persName> shall not be disturbed. The Imperial
					pleasure is hereby conveyed.
					<lb/><date when="1333-12-16">Gen-ko 3 y. 11 m. 9 d. [16 December 1333]</date>.
						<emph rend="italic"><seg xml:id="noteEn1-1-3">Shiki-bu dai-zho</seg></emph>,
						<span facs="#zone_nst_nky_r2b">(monogram)</span>.</p>

				<note target="#noteEn1-1-1" type="translatorsNotes">To-chi-gyo chi, land in actual
					holding.</note>

				<note target="#noteEn1-1-2" type="translatorsNotes">This is Shigemoto, the fourth
					lord of the Iriki-in.</note>
				<note target="#noteEn1-1-3" type="translatorsNotes">One who bore the official title
					dai-zho in the shiki-bu department. He transmits the imperial decree.</note>
			</div>
